The documents provide information about György Csányi being part of a team that won a bronze medal in the men's 4x100 metres relay event at the 1952 Summer Olympics. Specifically, the passage states:

- "At that time the Hungarian 4x100 relay was already formed, in which from 1951 György Csányi and Béla Goldoványi started alongside Zarándi and Varasdi, and received the name “lightning sticks”."
